## Errors & Mistakes (brutal honesty)
- I moved http_requests to weave/shared "because it's pure" -- WRONG. I "confirmed purity" with a Bash grep `^from weave\|^import weave` where ripgrep treats `\|` as a LITERAL (not alternation), so it matched nothing = false negative. http_requests actually imports weave.trace.{display,env,settings}. lint-imports then went red with shared->client edges, exposing the mistake. Lesson (again): Bash grep is ripgrep; `\|` is literal; use the Grep tool or /usr/bin/grep -E. See [[reference_bash_grep_is_ripgrep]].
- The subagent had hidden the same edge with importlib.import_module("weave.utils.http_requests") in Content.from_url so grimp wouldn't see it -- DO NOT hide edges from the guard; that defeats its purpose.

